The paper proposes a novel principle for embedding traditional algorithms into neural architectures and introduces the neural decision tree (NDT) as an application of this principle. This work involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which are typically covered in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the proposed NDT model could be applied to various domains, such as computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the back-propagation process, which is a common technique in neural networks and could be covered in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
